# Bipolar Disorders
Educational materials on bipolar disorders, focusing on clinically relevant concepts for learners and healthcare professionals.

## Purpose
- Summarize core features of bipolar disorders
- Support differential diagnosis and clinical assessment
- Provide structured, accessible content in Portuguese

## Planned subtopics
- Core symptoms and diagnostic criteria
- Manic, hypomanic, and depressive episodes
- Rapid cycling and mixed features
- Differential diagnosis
- Functional impact and risk assessment
- Overview of treatment strategies
- Patient and family education

> Note: Content in this repository is for educational purposes only and does not replace formal clinical training, local protocols, or individualized medical care.
